Hospital Corporation in New York

20:19.266 --> 20:23.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
City, they can't possibly
sustain these cuts to
the Medicaid budget.

20:23.366 --> 20:28.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Other hospitals that
have a large number of
Medicaid patients have
a very tiny margin.

20:29.466 --> 20:32.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That margin evaporates
with this bill.

20:32.033 --> 20:35.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And is that
-- even with tweaking,
you're saying there's
literally no way around?

20:36.933 --> 20:39.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

20:39.033 --> 20:41.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KENNETH DAVIS: Well,
fundamentally, this
bill is about decreasing
Medicaid and decreasing

20:41.233 --> 20:45.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
what states receive for
Medicaid and decreasing,
in the House case, those
who have the extended

20:47.366 --> 20:51.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
benefits or the eligibility that
they previously didn't have.

20:52.933 --> 20:55.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The bill isn't that much
around tweaks to Obamacare.

20:55.566 --> 20:57.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a little bit.

20:57.633 --> 21:00.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a bit to tweak the
exchanges, but the money's
coming from Medicaid.

21:00.966 --> 21:04.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And unless they take
a completely different
approach to Medicaid,
I don't see that tweaks

21:04.433 --> 21:06.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are going to help.

21:06.566 --> 21:08.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, there are
