cost-efficient way?

22:40.233 --> 22:42.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The system is failing us.

22:42.733 --> 22:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The macroeconomics of
health care are such
that the government can't
afford it, the states

22:46.266 --> 22:49.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can't afford it, the employers
can't afford it, and the
employees can't afford it.

22:49.800 --> 22:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What we have got to ask is,
what's wrong with the system
and how do we change it so that

22:54.200 --> 22:56.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
it's more efficient
for everybody?

22:56.066 --> 22:57.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You
brought up Medicaid.

22:57.633 --> 23:01.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You were saying how much of this
legislation is around Medicaid.

23:01.066 --> 23:06.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
