I'm in the right economy, which
America's definitely been ever

39:38.600 --> 39:39.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
since that time.

39:39.833 --> 39:42.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Dow has gone from
121000 during that time.

39:42.733 --> 39:47.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And no matter what the headlines
say, or terrible things are
happening -- we were losing the

39:49.033 --> 39:53.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
war in the Pacific when
I first bought stocks.

39:53.133 --> 39:56.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, America's going
to do fine over time.

39:56.400 --> 39:58.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
America business is going
to do fine over time.

39:58.666 --> 40:03.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Occasionally, we go off the
tracks with bubbles like -- and
a lot of human error and that

40:04.266 --> 40:05.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
sort of thing.

40:05.466 --> 40:07.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But it will never
permanently derail us.

40:07.400 --> 40:10.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I don't try and guess when
to get in and out of the market.

40:10.133 --> 40:12.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I have owned stocks
consistently since 1942.

40:12.500 --> 40:16.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I owned the -- I was
buying stocks the day
before the election.

40:16.100 --> 40:18.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was buying the same stocks
the day after election.

40:18.666 --> 40:21.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And if Hillary had been
elected, it would have
been the same thing.

40:21.200 --> 40:25.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Does President
Trump deserve credit for what
is going on right now in the

40:25.233 --> 40:27.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
market?

40:27.266 --> 40:31.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WARREN BUFFETT: I -- the
stock market has been going up
basically since March of 2009.

40:32.900 --> 40:35.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
